{
  "info": {
    "name": "Virtru DSP gRPC APIs",
    "description": "Comprehensive collection for interacting with Virtru Data Security Platform gRPC endpoints.\n\n**Services Included:**\n- Tagging PDP Service (v2)\n- Policy Artifact Service (v1)\n- NanoTDF Rewrap Service (v1)\n\n**Authentication:**\n1. Configure Keycloak variables in the Variables tab\n2. Run 'Get Access Token' request to authenticate\n3. Token is automatically saved and used for all subsequent requests\n4. Token auto-refresh on expiry",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "localhost:8080",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "gRPC server address (host:port)"
    },
    {
      "key": "keycloak_url",
      "value": "https://keycloak-ohalo.dsp-prod-green.virtru.com",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Keycloak base URL"
    },
    {
      "key": "keycloak_realm",
      "value": "dsp-ohalo",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Keycloak realm name"
    },
    {
      "key": "keycloak_client_id",
      "value": "dsp-outlook-auth",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "OAuth client ID"
    },
    {
      "key": "keycloak_username",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Your username"
    },
    {
      "key": "keycloak_password",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Your password"
    },
    {
      "key": "auth_token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Access token (auto-populated)"
    },
    {
      "key": "token_expires_at",
      "value": "0",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Token expiry timestamp (auto-populated)"
    },
    {
      "key": "use_tls",
      "value": "true",
      "type": "boolean",
      "description": "Use TLS for gRPC connections"
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{auth_token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Auto-refresh token if expired",
          "const tokenExpiresAt = parseInt(pm.collectionVariables.get('token_expires_at') || '0');",
          "const now = Date.now();",
          "",
          "if (now >= tokenExpiresAt) {",
          "    console.log('Token expired or missing, refreshing...');",
          "    ",
          "    const keycloakUrl = pm.collectionVariables.get('keycloak_url');",
          "    const realm = pm.collectionVariables.get('keycloak_realm');",
          "    const clientId = pm.collectionVariables.get('keycloak_client_id');",
          "    const username = pm.collectionVariables.get('keycloak_username');",
          "    const password = pm.collectionVariables.get('keycloak_password');",
          "    ",
          "    if (!username || !password) {",
          "        console.log('Username or password not set, skipping auto-refresh');",
          "        return;",
          "    }",
          "    ",
          "    const tokenUrl = `${keycloakUrl}/realms/${realm}/protocol/openid-connect/token`;",
          "    ",
          "    pm.sendRequest({",
          "        url: tokenUrl,",
          "        method: 'POST',",
          "        header: {",
          "            'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'",
          "        },",
          "        body: {",
          "            mode: 'urlencoded',",
          "            urlencoded: [",
          "                { key: 'grant_type', value: 'password' },",
          "                { key: 'client_id', value: clientId },",
          "                { key: 'username', value: username },",
          "                { key: 'password', value: password }",
          "            ]",
          "        }",
          "    }, (err, response) => {",
          "        if (err) {",
          "            console.error('Failed to refresh token:', err);",
          "            return;",
          "        }",
          "        ",
          "        const jsonResponse = response.json();",
          "        if (jsonResponse.access_token) {",
          "            pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_token', jsonResponse.access_token);",
          "            ",
          "            const expiresIn = jsonResponse.expires_in || 300;",
          "            const expiresAt = Date.now() + (expiresIn * 1000) - 60000; // 1 min buffer",
          "            pm.collectionVariables.set('token_expires_at', expiresAt.toString());",
          "            ",
          "            console.log('Token refreshed successfully');",
          "        }",
          "    });",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Authentication",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Access Token (Password Grant)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Save access token to collection variable",
                  "const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "if (jsonData.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_token', jsonData.access_token);",
                  "    ",
                  "    // Calculate expiry time",
                  "    const expiresIn = jsonData.expires_in || 300;",
                  "    const expiresAt = Date.now() + (expiresIn * 1000) - 60000; // 1 min buffer",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token_expires_at', expiresAt.toString());",
                  "    ",
                  "    console.log('Access token saved successfully');",
                  "    console.log('Token expires in:', expiresIn, 'seconds');",
                  "    ",
                  "    pm.test('Token obtained successfully', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(jsonData.access_token).to.exist;",
                  "    });",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.error('No access token in response');",
                  "    pm.test('Token request failed', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect.fail('No access_token in response');",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "password",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{keycloak_client_id}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "username",
                  "value": "{{keycloak_username}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "password",
                  "value": "{{keycloak_password}}",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{keycloak_url}}/realms/{{keycloak_realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": ["{{keycloak_url}}"],
              "path": ["realms", "{{keycloak_realm}}", "protocol", "openid-connect", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Get OAuth access token using password grant.\n\n**Required Variables:**\n- `keycloak_url`: Keycloak base URL\n- `keycloak_realm`: Realm name\n- `keycloak_client_id`: OAuth client ID\n- `keycloak_username`: Your username\n- `keycloak_password`: Your password\n\n**Auto-saves token** to `auth_token` variable for use in all requests."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Access Token (Client Credentials)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "if (jsonData.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_token', jsonData.access_token);",
                  "    ",
                  "    const expiresIn = jsonData.expires_in || 300;",
                  "    const expiresAt = Date.now() + (expiresIn * 1000) - 60000;",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token_expires_at', expiresAt.toString());",
                  "    ",
                  "    console.log('Client credentials token saved');",
                  "    pm.test('Token obtained', () => pm.expect(jsonData.access_token).to.exist);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "client_credentials",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{keycloak_client_id}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_secret",
                  "value": "{{keycloak_client_secret}}",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{keycloak_url}}/realms/{{keycloak_realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": ["{{keycloak_url}}"],
              "path": ["realms", "{{keycloak_realm}}", "protocol", "openid-connect", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Get OAuth access token using client credentials grant.\n\n**Use this for:**\n- Service accounts\n- Machine-to-machine authentication\n\n**Required Variables:**\n- `keycloak_client_id`: Service account client ID\n- `keycloak_client_secret`: Client secret"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "if (jsonData.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_token', jsonData.access_token);",
                  "    ",
                  "    if (jsonData.refresh_token) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', jsonData.refresh_token);",
                  "    }",
                  "    ",
                  "    const expiresIn = jsonData.expires_in || 300;",
                  "    const expiresAt = Date.now() + (expiresIn * 1000) - 60000;",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token_expires_at', expiresAt.toString());",
                  "    ",
                  "    console.log('Token refreshed');",
                  "    pm.test('Token refreshed', () => pm.expect(jsonData.access_token).to.exist);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "refresh_token",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{keycloak_client_id}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "refresh_token",
                  "value": "{{refresh_token}}",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{keycloak_url}}/realms/{{keycloak_realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": ["{{keycloak_url}}"],
              "path": ["realms", "{{keycloak_realm}}", "protocol", "openid-connect", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Refresh an existing access token.\n\n**Required:**\n- Previous token request must have returned a refresh_token\n- Refresh token must not be expired"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Authentication requests for obtaining OAuth tokens from Keycloak.\n\n**Quick Start:**\n1. Set credentials in Variables tab\n2. Run 'Get Access Token (Password Grant)'\n3. Token is auto-saved and used for all API calls\n\n**Auto-Refresh:**\nThe collection automatically refreshes expired tokens before each request."
    },
    {
      "name": "Tagging PDP Service",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Tag Content Items",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"items\": [\n    {\n      \"desc\": {\n        \"type\": \"text.plain\",\n        \"id\": \"content-1\",\n        \"name\": \"sample.txt\"\n      },\n      \"text\": \"This is a sample document with sensitive information.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"type\": \"document\",\n  \"options\": {\n    \"mode\": \"ALL\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/tagging.pdp.v2.TaggingPDPService/Tag",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["tagging.pdp.v2.TaggingPDPService", "Tag"]
            },
            "description": "Process content items through the PDP to produce tags.\n\n**Request Fields:**\n- `items`: Array of ContentItem objects\n- `type`: Optional top-level content type\n- `options`: TagRequestOptions with processing mode\n\n**Modes:**\n- ALL: Process all stages\n- TAG_EXTRACT: Content extraction + tag extraction\n- TAG_EXTRACT_AND_PROCESS: Extraction + processing\n- EXTRACT_GENERATE_TOKENS: Generate encrypted tokens"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Tag Per Content Item",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"items\": [\n    {\n      \"desc\": {\n        \"type\": \"email.header\",\n        \"id\": \"email-1\",\n        \"metadata\": {\n          \"from\": \"sender@example.com\",\n          \"to\": \"recipient@example.com\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"text\": \"Subject: Confidential Report\\nFrom: sender@example.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"desc\": {\n        \"type\": \"email.body.text\",\n        \"id\": \"email-2\"\n      },\n      \"text\": \"This email contains classified information about Project Alpha.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"options\": {\n    \"mode\": \"TAG_EXTRACT_AND_PROCESS\"\n  }\n}",
